feed.title: Foxx Development updates share count and ownership for annual meeting By Investing.com
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. has provided updated share count and ownership details ahead of its 2025 Annual Meeting of Stockholders. feed.title: Foxx Development updates share count and ownership for annual meeting
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. (NASDAQ:FOXX) has released supplemental disclosures ahead of its 2025 Annual Meeting, scheduled for December 22, 2025. The company updated its outstanding share count to 7,058,727 as of November 28, 2025, and provided details on beneficial ownership, including significant stakes held by Acri Capital Sponsor LLC, BRR Investment Corp., and New Bay Capital Limited. The firm also clarified that director nominee Ms. Michelle Jie Shen is 50 years old and stated that the annual meeting's location, purpose, and proposals remain unchanged.

feed.title: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. SEC 10-Q Report
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. (FOXX) has released its Q3 Form 10-Q report, detailing financial performance and operational highlights. The report shows a decrease in revenue but improved cost management leading to a significant increase in gross profit and reduced operating losses, despite a higher net loss due to interest expenses. The company is focusing on addressing liquidity challenges through various financing options.

feed.title: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. Reports Earnings Results for the Full Year Ended June 30, 2025 - MarketScreener
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. announced its financial results for the full year ended June 30, 2025, reporting a significant increase in sales to USD 65.92 million from USD 3.23 million a year ago. Despite the sales growth, the company's net loss widened to USD 9.02 million from USD 3.43 million in the previous year. Basic and diluted loss per share from continuing operations also increased to USD 1.47, up from USD 1.04 previously.

feed.title: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. SEC 10-K Report - TradingView
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. has released its annual 10-K report, highlighting substantial revenue growth of 1,941.8% to $65.9 million, primarily driven by new wholesale customers and product launches in mobile phones and wearable electronics. Despite this growth, the company reported increased losses from operations and net losses due to higher operating expenses. The report details strategic initiatives for market expansion, capital management, and addresses significant operational, market, and financial risks.

feed.title: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. to Join Russell Microcap® Index, Marking a Key Milestone in Company Growth
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. announced its inclusion in the Russell Microcap® Index effective June 27, 2025, a significant milestone expected to boost its visibility among institutional investors and enhance liquidity. CEO Greg Foley highlighted that this recognition validates the company's financial performance and innovations in consumer electronics and IoT solutions. The inclusion will facilitate potential expansion efforts by attracting specialized institutional investment.

feed.title: FreeCast Enters Distribution Partnership with Consumer Electronics and IoT Company Foxx Development
feed.summary: FreeCast and Foxx Development have announced a new distribution agreement, bringing FreeCast’s free streaming app to hundreds of thousands of smartphones and tablets manufactured by Foxx Development. The partnership will see the FreeCast app pre-loaded on Foxx devices, particularly benefiting users of the National Lifeline Program and Affordable Connectivity Program. Both companies anticipate a significant reach to consumers looking for affordable and comprehensive streaming solutions.

feed.title: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. to Ring Nasdaq Closing Bell on January 3, 2025, Celebrating Public Transition and Business Growth
feed.summary: Foxx Development Holdings Inc. announced it will ring the Nasdaq Closing Bell on January 3, 2025, to celebrate its public transition in September 2024 and ongoing business growth. CEO Greg Foley will lead the ceremony, emphasizing the company's dedication to sustainable growth and innovative IoT solutions. The event will be broadcast live, highlighting the company's achievements to a broad audience.
